## 5. Approved Algorithms (minimums)
| Use | Approved | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Symmetric encryption | AES-256 (GCM preferred) | Default for data at rest. |
| Asymmetric / key exchange | RSA ≥ 3072, or ECC P-256/P-384 | |
| Hashing (integrity) | SHA-256 / SHA-384 | SHA-1/MD5 prohibited for security use. |
| Password storage | bcrypt / scrypt / Argon2id / PBKDF2 (high iterations) | Salted; never reversible encryption. |
| Transport | TLS [1.2]+ with modern cipher suites; TLS 1.3 preferred | TLS ≤ 1.1 disabled. |
[Review against current NIST/industry guidance at each annual review.]

## 6. Key & Secret Lifecycle
- **Generation:** Keys generated within [AWS KMS]/HSM; sufficient entropy; never in application code.
- **Storage:** KMS-managed CMKs ([customer-managed keys] for PHI-bearing data); secrets in [Secrets Manager]/[SSM SecureString]; no plaintext export.
- **Distribution/use:** Access via IAM/KMS key policies, least privilege; envelope encryption for data keys.
- **Rotation:** Automatic annual rotation for KMS CMKs [enable]; secrets rotated every [90 days / on schedule] and on compromise; rotate immediately on suspected exposure or relevant offboarding.
- **Revocation/destruction:** Disable/schedule deletion of keys when retired; document destruction; ensure data dependent on a destroyed key is also retired (crypto-shredding may be used for secure deletion).
- **Service-specific:** [Snowflake] uses hierarchical key model with automatic rotation; [Tri-Secret Secure / CMK] where required. [RDS], S3, EBS use KMS-backed encryption with default-on settings (`configuration-and-hardening-standard.md.template`).

## 7. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer] and [CTO], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log. Use of any non-approved algorithm requires explicit approval.

## 8. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Compliance is verified through [AWS Config]/[Security Hub] checks (encryption enabled, TLS policies), KMS/CloudTrail key-usage review, secret-scanning results, and TLS configuration scans, reviewed during internal audit. Detection of hardcoded secrets triggers rotation and incident response (`../resilience/incident-response-plan.md.template`). Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

